# Drop your district shapefile (.shp, .shx, .dbf, .prj) or GeoJSON here.
#
# Recommended sources:
#   - Datameet India Maps: https://github.com/datameet/maps
#   - Survey of India / NCOG: https://onlinemaps.surveyofindia.gov.in
#   - GADM (gadm.org) — level-2 gives districts
#
# IMPORTANT: Note the boundary vintage year of your shapefile.
# Post-2011 district splits (e.g. Telangana, many UP/MP/Bihar splits)
# will not appear in a 2011-boundary shapefile.
